(14, 'Software Developer', 'sortout innovation', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 10000, 12000, 'Full Time', '0-1', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are looking for a skilled Zoho Developer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience in developing, customizing, and integrating Zoho applications, including Zoho CRM, Zoho Creator, Zoho Books, Zoho Projects, and Zoho Flow. You will be responsible for automating business processes, creating custom modules, and enhancing the Zoho ecosystem to improve productivity and business efficiency.\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nDesign and develop custom functions and workflows in Zoho Creator, Zoho CRM, and other Zoho apps using Deluge scripting.\r\n\r\nIntegrate Zoho apps with third-party systems using REST APIs or Zoho Flow.\r\n\r\nCustomize Zoho CRM modules, layouts, templates, dashboards, and reports as per business needs.\r\n\r\nAutomate lead management, sales processes, and customer engagement workflows.\r\n\r\nCreate and maintain custom reports and dashboards to analyze KPIs and business metrics.\r\n\r\nTroubleshoot and resolve application issues and bugs.\r\n\r\nWork with cross-functional teams (sales, marketing, operations) to understand and implement requirements.\r\n\r\nStay updated with Zoho’s latest updates, new modules, and best practices.\r\n\r\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.\r\n\r\n1–3 years of hands-on experience with Zoho suite (CRM, Creator, Books, Projects, etc.).\r\n\r\nStrong knowledge of Deluge scripting, Zoho APIs, and custom workflows.\r\n\r\nExperience with integration tools like Zoho Flow, Zapier, or custom API integration.\r\n\r\nFamiliarity with JavaScript, HTML/CSS, and SQL is a plus.\r\n\r\nStrong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.\r\n\r\nExcellent communication and documentation skills.\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications:\r\nZoho Certified Developer (optional but preferred).\r\n\r\nExperience in developing automation in Zoho using functions and schedules.\r\n\r\nKnowledge of CRM best practices and data security principles.\r\n\r\nPrevious experience in a SaaS-based or startup environment.', 'IT & Software Development', 5, 1, '', 'B2, 551-C, 5th floor, Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-10 11:43:14', NULL),
(15, 'Zoho Developer', 'sortout innovation', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 18000, 25000, 'Full Time', '1 - 2 years', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are seeking a Zoho Developer with 1–2 years of hands-on experience in designing and implementing solutions using the Zoho suite of applications. The ideal candidate will have a good understanding of business workflows and can effectively automate and integrate processes using Zoho tools like Zoho CRM, Creator, Books, and Desk.\r\n\r\nRoles & Responsibilities:\r\nDesign, build, and maintain custom modules, workflows, reports, and dashboards within Zoho applications.\r\n\r\nWrite Deluge scripts to automate complex business logic in Zoho CRM and Creator.\r\n\r\nIntegrate Zoho apps with third-party tools using APIs, Webhooks, and Zoho Flow.\r\n\r\nWork closely with internal teams (Sales, Marketing, Finance) to gather requirements and implement solutions.\r\n\r\nCustomize email templates, reports, and layout rules to streamline operations.\r\n\r\nDebug, troubleshoot, and enhance existing solutions in Zoho.\r\n\r\nRequired Skills:\r\n1–2 years of experience in Zoho CRM, Zoho Creator, and other Zoho applications.\r\n\r\nStrong command over Deluge scripting, Zoho CRM automation, and workflow management.\r\n\r\nBasic knowledge of REST APIs, HTML, and JavaScript.\r\n\r\nAbility to translate business needs into technical solutions.\r\n\r\nStrong communication and team collaboration skills.\r\n\r\nDetail-oriented with a focus on writing clean and scalable code.\r\n\r\n✅ Preferred Skills:\r\nZoho Certifications (CRM/Creator Developer).\r\n\r\nExperience with Zoho Books, Desk, Projects, Flow, or Zoho Analytics.\r\n\r\nPrevious experience in client communication or stakeholder interaction.\r\n\r\nExposure to third-party integrations (e.g., Google Apps, payment gateways, etc.).', 'IT & Software Development', 8, 1, '', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-10 11:50:38', NULL),
(16, 'Telesales Executive', 'Life chart and Petnojo', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 14000, 20000, 'Full Time', '1 - 2 years', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are looking for a highly motivated Telesales Executive with 2–3 years of proven experience in sales over the phone. The ideal candidate will be responsible for contacting potential customers, generating leads, explaining products or services, and closing sales to meet business targets.\r\n\r\nRoles & Responsibilities:\r\nMake outbound calls to prospective clients to promote products/services.\r\nUnderstand customer needs and present appropriate solutions.\r\nFollow up on leads through calls, emails, and WhatsApp.\r\nAchieve daily, weekly, and monthly sales targets.\r\nMaintain accurate records of calls, customer details, and sales data in CRM.\r\nHandle customer objections confidently and convert them into successful sales.\r\nCollaborate with the sales and marketing teams for campaign strategies.\r\nProvide excellent customer service and support to build long-term relationships.\r\n\r\nRequired Skills:\r\n2–3 years of telesales or inside sales experience (B2C or B2B).\r\nExcellent verbal communication and convincing skills in [English/Hindi or local language].\r\nStrong listening skills and customer-centric approach.\r\nBasic knowledge of CRM systems and Microsoft Office tools.\r\nTarget-driven with the ability to handle pressure.\r\nPositive attitude, confident, and persistent.\r\n\r\nPreferred Skills:\r\nExperience in the [industry – e.g., EdTech, Insurance, Real Estate, Finance, etc.].\r\nMultilingual ability is a plus.\r\nStrong negotiation and closing techniques.\r\nFamiliarity with digital sales tools (Zoom, WhatsApp Business, email marketing tools).', 'Sales & Business Development', 9, 1, '', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-10 12:14:06', NULL),
(17, 'Team Lead (Telesales)', 'Life chart', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 30000, 35000, 'Full Time', '2 - 4 years', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are seeking a dynamic and experienced Telesales Team Lead to manage and motivate our telesales team. The ideal candidate will have 2–4 years of experience in telesales or inside sales, with at least 1 year in a leadership or supervisory role. You’ll be responsible for driving team performance, meeting targets, providing training, and improving conversion rates.\r\n\r\nRoles & Responsibilities:\r\nLead, coach, and manage a team of telesales executives to achieve daily, weekly, and monthly sales targets.\r\nMonitor team performance using KPIs such as call volume, conversion rate, and lead quality.\r\nProvide regular training, guidance, and support to enhance team productivity and product knowledge.\r\nConduct daily team meetings and motivational sessions to keep the team engaged and focused.\r\nTrack individual performance, give constructive feedback, and handle escalations.\r\nGenerate sales reports and present updates to senior management.\r\nCollaborate with the marketing and product teams to improve pitch strategies and lead quality.\r\nMaintain CRM data hygiene and ensure timely follow-ups by the team.\r\n\r\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\r\n2–4 years of experience in telesales or inside sales.\r\nAt least 1 year of team handling or leadership experience.\r\nStrong knowledge of sales techniques, objection handling, and closing strategies.\r\nExcellent communication, leadership, and motivational skills.\r\nProficient in using CRM tools, Excel, and sales dashboards.\r\nGoal-oriented and comfortable working in a target-driven environment.\r\n\r\nPreferred Skills:\r\nExperience in sectors like EdTech, Insurance, Real Estate, or FinTech.\r\nMultilingual ability is a plus.\r\nExperience in reporting, team KPI analysis, and sales forecasting.\r\nAbility to handle pressure and manage multiple priorities.', 'Sales & Business Development', 6, 1, '', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-10 12:20:17', NULL),
(18, 'Web Developer', 'Business raisers', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 15000, 20000, 'Full Time', '2 - 4 years', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are looking for a passionate and detail-oriented Web Developer with 1–2 years of experience in developing responsive and dynamic websites. The ideal candidate should have strong skills in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and experience working with frameworks/libraries such as Bootstrap, React.js, or jQuery. You will be responsible for developing front-end components and working closely with designers and backend teams to bring ideas to life.\r\n\r\nRoles & Responsibilities:\r\nDevelop and maintain responsive websites and web applications.\r\nWrite clean, efficient, and well-documented code using HTML, CSS, JavaScript (and related libraries).\r\nConvert UI/UX designs from tools like Figma or Adobe XD into functional web pages.\r\nEnsure website performance, responsiveness, and cross-browser compatibility.\r\nWork with backend developers to integrate APIs and handle dynamic content.\r\nTroubleshoot bugs, test performance, and optimize page speed and user experience.\r\nKeep up to date with the latest trends and best practices in web development.\r\n\r\nRequired Skills:\r\n1–2 years of experience in web development.\r\nStrong command over HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript.\r\nFamiliarity with Bootstrap or other CSS frameworks.\r\nBasic understanding of React.js, jQuery, or similar JS libraries.\r\nKnowledge of version control systems (e.g., Git).\r\nGood debugging and browser developer tools skills.\\\r\nStrong problem-solving and communication skills.', 'IT & Software Development', 12, 1, '', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-10 12:27:15', NULL),
(19, 'Business Development Executive', 'Business raisers', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 20000, 25000, 'Full Time', '2 - 4 years', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are looking for a highly driven and result-oriented Business Development Executive with 2–4 years of experience in identifying new business opportunities, managing client relationships, and driving revenue growth. The ideal candidate should be confident in generating leads, closing deals, and working closely with the marketing and product teams to align sales strategies.\r\n\r\nRoles & Responsibilities:\r\nIdentify and pursue new business opportunities through cold calls, emails, LinkedIn, and networking.\r\nDevelop and maintain strong relationships with clients, prospects, and key stakeholders.\r\nUnderstand client needs and present tailored business solutions.\r\nCreate proposals, pitch decks, and presentations to effectively showcase offerings.\r\nAchieve sales targets and contribute to overall revenue growth.\r\nConduct market research to identify trends, competitors, and potential clients.\r\nMaintain a pipeline of leads in CRM and provide regular updates on outreach and conversion.\r\nCollaborate with marketing, product, and operations teams to improve the sales process and customer experience.\r\n\r\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\r\n2–4 years of experience in business development, sales, or client acquisition.\r\nProven track record of meeting or exceeding sales targets.\r\nExcellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills.\r\nStrong negotiation and closing skills.\r\nProficiency in tools like CRM software, MS Office, and Google Workspace.\r\nAbility to work independently and as part of a collaborative team.\r\nBachelor’s degree in Business, Marketing, or a related field.\r\n\r\nPreferred Skills:\r\nExperience in B2B or SaaS-based selling (optional, based on company).\r\nPrior experience in [Industry – EdTech, IT, Real Estate, Marketing, etc.].\r\nKnowledge of lead generation tools (LinkedIn Sales Navigator, Apollo, etc.).\r\nComfortable with data analysis and business intelligence tools.', 'Sales & Business Development', 5, 1, '', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-10 12:41:39', NULL),
(20, 'Marketing & Communication', 'DNS TECHNOCRAFT', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 40000, 50000, 'Full Time', '1 - 2 years', 'All Education levels', 'We are seeking a creative and driven Marketing & Communication Executive with 1–2 years of experience to support the planning and execution of marketing campaigns, content creation, and brand communication strategies. The ideal candidate will have a strong understanding of digital marketing tools, excellent written and verbal communication skills, and a passion for storytelling and branding.\r\n\r\nRoles & Responsibilities:\r\nAssist in planning and executing integrated marketing campaigns across online and offline channels.\r\nCreate engaging content for social media, blogs, emails, website, and marketing materials.\r\nManage the company’s social media presence and monitor engagement metrics.\r\nCoordinate with designers, content creators, and external agencies to deliver brand-aligned assets.\r\nEnsure consistent brand messaging across all communication platforms.\r\nSupport internal communications, PR efforts, and event coordination.\r\nTrack and analyze the performance of campaigns using analytics tools.\r\nMaintain and update marketing calendars, newsletters, and media lists.\r\n\r\n Required Skills & Qualifications:\r\n1–2 years of experience in marketing, communications, or related roles.\r\nStrong verbal and written communication skills in English.\r\nProficiency in social media platforms, content writing, and email marketing tools.\r\nBasic knowledge of SEO, Google Analytics, and marketing automation tools (Mailchimp, HubSpot, etc.).\r\nCreative mindset with attention to detail.\r\nBachelor\'s degree in Marketing, Communications, Mass Media, or a related field.\r\n\r\nPreferred Skills:\r\nExperience in tools like Canva, Adobe Suite, or Figma.\r\nFamiliarity with CMS platforms like WordPress.\r\nExposure to branding, storytelling, and influencer marketing.\r\nPrevious experience in handling internal/external communications or PR.', 'Marketing & Advertising', 15, 1, '', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-10 12:49:19', NULL),
(21, 'CRM (Logistics)', 'Arena', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 25000, 35000, 'Full Time', '1 - 2 years', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are seeking a motivated and detail-oriented CRM Logistics Specialist to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for managing and optimizing our Customer Relationship Management (CRM) system to enhance logistics operations and improve customer satisfaction. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless integration between customer data and supply chain processes.\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nMaintain and update the CRM system with accurate customer and logistics information.​\r\nCoordinate with the logistics team to ensure timely order fulfillment and delivery.​\r\nAnalyze customer data to identify trends and opportunities for process improvement.​\r\nGenerate reports on logistics performance and customer satisfaction metrics.​\r\nAssist in the development and implementation of CRM strategies to enhance customer engagement.​\r\nProvide training and support to team members on CRM system usage.\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\nBachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Supply Chain Management, Information Technology, or a related field.​\r\n1–2 years of experience in a CRM or logistics role.​\r\nProficiency in CRM software (e.g., Salesforce, HubSpot) and Microsoft Office Suite.​\r\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills.​\r\nExcellent communication and interpersonal abilities.​\r\nAbility to work collaboratively in a team environment.\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications:\r\nExperience with logistics software or ERP systems.​\r\nKnowledge of supply chain processes and best practices.​\r\nCertification in CRM or supply chain management.\r\n\r\nWhy Join Us:\r\nOpportunity to work in a dynamic and growing industry.​\r\nCollaborative and supportive team environment.​\r\nContinuous learning and professional development opportunities.​\r\nCompetitive salary and benefits package.', 'Operations & Supply Chain Management', 8, 1, '', '', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-11 05:33:03', NULL),
(22, 'Business Development Manager', 'Arena', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 25000, 35000, 'Full Time', '2 - 5 years', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'We are seeking a proactive and results-driven Business Development Manager to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have 2–5 years of experience in business development or sales, with a proven track record of driving revenue growth and forging strong client relationships. This role involves identifying new business opportunities, developing strategic partnerships, and contributing to the company\'s overall growth objectives.​\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nIdentify and pursue new business opportunities through market research, networking, and outreach.​\r\nDevelop and maintain relationships with prospective and existing clients to foster long-term partnerships.​\r\nCollaborate with internal teams to develop proposals and presentations tailored to client needs.​\r\nNegotiate contracts and close agreements to maximize profits.​\r\nMonitor market trends and competitor activities to inform business strategies.​\r\nAchieve sales targets and contribute to the company\'s revenue growth.​\r\nMaintain accurate records of sales activities and client interactions in the CRM system.\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\nBachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Marketing, or a related field.​\r\n2–5 years of experience in business development, sales, or a related role.​\r\nStrong understanding of sales principles and customer relationship management.​\r\nExcellent communication, negotiation, and interpersonal skills.​\r\nProficiency in CRM software and Microsoft Office Suite.​\r\nAbility to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment.\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications:\r\nExperience in the [specific industry, e.g., technology, healthcare, finance].​\r\nFamiliarity with digital marketing and lead generation strategies.​\r\nMBA or relevant professional certifications.\r\n\r\nWhy Join Us:\r\nOpportunity to work with a passionate and innovative team.​\r\nCompetitive salary and performance-based incentives.​\r\nProfessional development and career advancement opportunities.​\r\nInclusive and collaborative work culture.', 'Sales & Business Development', 8, 1, '', '', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-11 05:48:00', NULL),
(23, 'Accountant', 'Arena', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 20000, 30000, 'Full Time', '5 - 7 years', 'All Education levels', 'We are seeking a detail-oriented and experienced Accountant to join our finance team. The ideal candidate will have 2–5 years of experience in accounting, with a strong understanding of financial principles and practices. This role involves managing financial records, ensuring compliance with regulations, and contributing to the company\'s financial health.\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nPrepare and maintain accurate financial records, including ledgers, journals, and balance sheets.​\r\nReconcile bank statements and resolve discrepancies promptly.​\r\nAssist in the preparation of monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports.​\r\nEnsure compliance with accounting standards and regulatory requirements.​\r\nManage accounts payable and receivable processes.​\r\nSupport internal and external audits by providing necessary documentation and explanations.​\r\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to support budgeting and forecasting activities.​\r\nStay updated on changes in financial regulations and best practices.\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\nBachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.​\r\n2–5 years of experience in accounting or finance roles.​\r\nProficiency in accounting software (e.g., Tally, QuickBooks, SAP) and Microsoft Excel.​\r\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills.​\r\nExcellent attention to detail and organizational abilities.​\r\nGood communication skills, both written and verbal.\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications:\r\nProfessional certifications such as CA (Chartered Accountant) or CMA (Certified Management Accountant) are a plus.​\r\nExperience with GST, TDS, and other Indian taxation processes.​\r\nFamiliarity with financial reporting standards applicable in India.\r\n\r\nWhy Join Us:\r\nOpportunity to work in a dynamic and growth-oriented environment.​\r\nCollaborative team culture that values innovation and integrity.​\r\nContinuous learning and professional development opportunities.​\r\nCompetitive compensation and benefits package.', 'Finance & Accounting', 6, 1, '', '', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-11 06:17:08', NULL),
(24, 'Graphic Designer', 'Arena', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 20000, 25000, 'Full Time', '2 - 3', 'All Education levels', 'We are seeking a creative and detail-oriented Graphic Designer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have 2–5 years of experience in graphic design, with a strong portfolio showcasing a range of design projects. This role involves collaborating with cross-functional teams to create visually compelling designs that align with our brand identity and marketing objectives.​\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nDesign and produce high-quality graphics for digital and print media, including websites, social media, advertisements, brochures, and presentations.​\r\nCollaborate with the marketing team to develop creative concepts and campaigns.​\r\nEnsure consistency of brand visuals across all platforms and materials.​\r\nManage multiple design projects simultaneously, meeting deadlines and maintaining attention to detail.​\r\nStay updated with industry trends and incorporate best practices into design work.​\r\nPrepare and present design concepts to stakeholders for feedback and approval.​\r\nWork closely with external vendors and printers to ensure the quality of final outputs.\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\nBachelor’s degree in Graphic Design, Visual Arts, or a related field.​\r\n2–5 years of professional experience in graphic design.​\r\nProficiency in design software such as Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign).​\r\nStrong understanding of design principles, typography, color theory, and layout techniques.​\r\nExcellent communication and interpersonal skills.​\r\nAbility to take constructive feedback and adapt designs accordingly.​\r\nA strong portfolio demonstrating a range of design projects and creativity.\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications:\r\nExperience with motion graphics and video editing software (e.g., After Effects, Premiere Pro).​\r\nFamiliarity with web design and basic knowledge of HTML/CSS.​\r\nUnderstanding of user experience (UX) and user interface (UI) design principles.​\r\nExperience working in a fast-paced, collaborative environment.', 'Other', 6, 1, '', '', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-11 06:25:40', NULL),
(25, 'Vendor Manager (Logistics)', 'Arena', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 35000, 40000, 'Full Time', '5 - 7', 'High School', 'We are seeking an experienced and strategic Vendor Manager to oversee our logistics partnerships. The ideal candidate will have 5–7 years of experience in vendor management within the logistics sector, demonstrating a strong ability to negotiate contracts, manage vendor relationships, and optimize supply chain operations. This role is pivotal in ensuring that our logistics vendors meet performance standards, comply with contractual obligations, and contribute to our overall operational efficiency.​\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nVendor Relationship Management: Develop and maintain strong relationships with logistics vendors, ensuring alignment with company objectives and performance expectations.​\r\nContract Negotiation: Negotiate terms and conditions with vendors to secure favorable pricing, service levels, and delivery timelines.​\r\nPerformance Monitoring: Establish and track key performance indicators (KPIs) to assess vendor performance, implementing corrective actions as necessary.​\r\nCompliance and Risk Management: Ensure vendors adhere to contractual obligations and regulatory requirements, conducting regular audits and assessments.​\r\nCollaboration: Work closely with internal departments such as procurement, operations, and finance to align vendor strategies with business needs.​\r\nProcess Improvement: Identify opportunities to streamline vendor management processes, enhancing efficiency and reducing costs.​\r\nReporting: Prepare and present regular reports on vendor performance, contract status, and risk assessments to senior management.​\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\nEducation: Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain Management, Business Administration, or a related field.​\r\nExperience: 5–7 years of experience in vendor management within the logistics industry.​\r\n\r\nSkills:\r\nStrong negotiation and contract management skills.​\r\nExcellent analytical and problem-solving abilities.​\r\nProficiency in vendor management software and Microsoft Office Suite.​\r\nExceptional communication and interpersonal skills.​\r\nAbility to manage multiple vendors and projects simultaneously.​\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications:\r\nProfessional certifications such as Certified Professional in Supply Management (CPSM) or Certified Supply Chain Professional (CSCP).​\r\nExperience with international logistics and global vendor management.​\r\nFamiliarity with ERP systems and logistics software.', 'Operations & Supply Chain Management', 3, 1, '', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', '', 5, '9', 1, 0, '2025-04-11 06:36:12', NULL),
(26, 'Field Sales Executive', 'sortout innovation', 'Spaze i-Tech Park, Gurugram, India', 15000, 17000, 'Full Time', '3 - 4 years', 'High School', 'We are seeking a dynamic and results-driven Field Sales Executive to join our logistics team. The ideal candidate will have 3–4 years of experience in logistics sales, with a proven track record of meeting and exceeding sales targets. This role involves identifying new business opportunities, maintaining client relationships, and contributing to the company\'s growth in the logistics sector.\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nBusiness Development: Identify and pursue new business opportunities in the logistics sector to expand the customer base.​\r\nClient Relationship Management: Maintain and strengthen relationships with existing clients, ensuring high levels of customer satisfaction.​\r\nSales Targets: Achieve and exceed monthly and quarterly sales targets set by the management.​\r\nMarket Analysis: Analyze market trends and competitor activities to identify potential areas for growth.​\r\nReporting: Prepare and submit regular sales reports, forecasts, and market feedback to the management team.​\r\nCollaboration: Work closely with the operations and customer service teams to ensure seamless service delivery to clients.\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\nEducation: Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Marketing, Logistics, or a related field.​\r\nExperience: 3–4 years of experience in field sales, preferably in the logistics or transportation industry.​\r\n\r\nSkills:\r\nStrong communication and interpersonal skills.​\r\nAbility to work independently and as part of a team.​\r\nProficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and CRM software.​\r\nExcellent negotiation and problem-solving abilities.​\r\nWillingness to travel extensively within the assigned territory.​\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications:\r\nExperience with logistics software and tools.​\r\nKnowledge of supply chain management principles.​\r\nAdditional certifications in